{{Quote|Jedi business, go back to your drinks.|Anakin Skywalker, to Civ Sila and other clubgoers|audio=Anakin-JediBusiness-AOTC.flac|<ref name="AoTC" />}}
'''Civ Sila''' was a [[Human/Legends|Human]] with [[Color/Legends|light]] skin and dark [[Hair/Legends|hair]].<ref name="AoTC" /> Sila was friends with the Humans [[Dixon Just]]<ref name="CSWE1">{{CSWECite|II|183|Just, Dixon}}</ref> and [[Zey Nep]],<ref name="zn">{{DB|character|zeynep|Nep, Zey}}</ref> and an associate of<ref name="CSWE2">{{CSWECite|III|42|Pratuhr, Artuo}}</ref> the [[Archaeologist/Legends|archaeologist]]<ref name="sn">{{DB|character|seibnod|Nod, Seib}}</ref> [[Artuo Pratuhr]].<ref name="CSWE2" /> Dixon and Nep were often found in Sila's company.<ref name="CSWE1" /><ref name="zn" /> During a [[Local day/Legends|night]]<ref name="AoTC" /> in [[22 BBY/Legends|22 BBY]],<ref name="NEC">''[[The New Essential Chronology]]'' dates the events of {{Film|II}} to [[22 BBY/Legends|22 BBY]].</ref> Sila, alongside Just, Nep, and Prathur, visited the [[Outlander Club/Legends|Outlander Club]],<ref name="AoTC" /> a [[Nightclub/Legends|nightclub]] and [[Gambling/Legends|gambling]] hall<ref name="CSWE3">{{CSWECite|II|431|Outlander Club}}</ref> located in the [[Uscru Entertainment District/Legends|Uscru Entertainment District]]<ref name="CSWE3" /> of the [[Planet/Legends|planet]]<ref name="TVD">''[[Star Wars: Attack of the Clones: The Visual Dictionary]]''</ref> [[Coruscant/Legends|Coruscant]],<ref name="CSWE3" /> as [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] [[Obi-Wan Kenobi/Legends|Obi-Wan Kenobi]] and [[Anakin Skywalker/Legends|Anakin Skywalker]] entered, [[Plot to assassinate Senator Amidala/Legends|searching]] for the [[Bounty hunter/Legends|bounty hunter]] [[Zam Wesell/Legends|Zam Wesell]].<ref name="AoTC" /> 

Sila approached Just near the entrance of the club, and the two talked. Soon after, Sila talked to Just, Nep, and Pratuhr near the club's bar. As Skywalker searched the club for Wesell,<ref name="AoTC" /> Sila debated with Just.<ref name="Insider">{{InsiderCite|75|Who's Who in the Outlander Club: It's Ladies' Night}}</ref> Sila later watched as Wesell was disarmed by Kenobi and taken out of the club. As Kenobi did so, Skywalker told the clubgoers to go back to their drinks. Sila wore dark [[Clothing/Legends|clothing]] at the club.<ref name="AoTC" />

==Behind the scenes==
{{Quote|Taking the role of Civ Sila, Trevor Tighe joins the Droid Unit on their night out on the town.|Daniel Wallace|<ref name="Insider" />}}
Civ Sila first appeared in the [[prequel trilogy]] film [[Star Wars: Episode II Attack of the Clones|''Star Wars'': Episode II ''Attack of the Clones'']],<ref name="AoTC">{{Film|II}}</ref> which released on [[May 16]], [[2002]].<ref name="Year">''[[Star Wars Year By Year: A Visual History, New Edition]]''</ref> The character was portrayed by [[Trevor Tighe]], a member of the film's Droid Unit crew.<ref name="Insider" /> The Outlander Club scenes including Sila were shot at [[Fox Studios, Sydney]] on [[July 17]], [[2000]].<ref name="Mythmaking">''[[Mythmaking: Behind the Scenes of Attack of the Clones]]''</ref> Before the film's release, the character was first pictured<ref name="TVD" /> on [[April 23]], 2002,<ref name="Amazon">{{SWArchive|url=eu/lit/ref/news20020227.html|text=Book Preview: DK Episode II Books}}</ref><ref name="ScrapbookRelease">{{SWArchive|url=eu/news/2002/04/news20020426.html|text=Episode II Books from Random House}}</ref> with the release of ''[[Star Wars: Attack of the Clones: The Visual Dictionary]]'', written by [[David West Reynolds (real person)|David West Reynolds]],<ref name="TVD" /> and in the ''[[Star Wars: Attack of the Clones Scrapbook]]'', written by [[Ryder Windham]].<ref name="Scrapbook">''[[Star Wars: Attack of the Clones Scrapbook]]''</ref> Sila was first named in the article "[[Who's Who in the Outlander Club: It's Ladies' Night]]" written by [[Daniel Wallace]], which was published in the [[Star Wars Insider 75|seventy-fifth issue]] of the ''[[Star Wars Insider]]'' magazine<ref name="Insider" /> on [[April 6]], [[2004]].<ref name="SW.com">{{SWArchive|url=community/fanclub/mag/news20040315.html|text=The New Face of Evil}}</ref>

